466 /// Print the basic block's name as: ----
467 /// ----
468 /// bb.{number}[.{ir-name}] [(attributes...)] ----
469 /// ----
470 /// The {ir-name} is only printed when the \ref PrintNameIr flag is passed ----
471 /// (which is the default). If the IR block has no name, it is identified ----
472 /// numerically using the attribute syntax as "(%ir-block.{ir-slot})". ----
473 /// ----
474 /// When the \ref PrintNameAttributes flag is passed, additional attributes ----
475 /// of the block are printed when set. ----
476 /// ----
477 /// \param printNameFlags Combination of \ref PrintNameFlag flags indicating ----
478 /// the parts to print. ----
479 /// \param moduleSlotTracker Optional ModuleSlotTracker. This method will ----
480 /// incorporate its own tracker when necessary to ----
481 /// determine the block's IR name. ----
482 void MachineBasicBlock::printName(raw_ostream &os, unsigned printNameFlags, 0
483 ModuleSlotTracker *moduleSlotTracker) const { ----
484 os << "bb." << getNumber(); 0
485 bool hasAttributes = false; 0
486 ----
487 auto PrintBBRef = [&](const BasicBlock *bb) { 0
488 os << "%ir-block."; 0
489 if (bb->hasName()) { 0
490 os << bb->getName(); 0
491 } else { ----
492 int slot = -1; 0
493 ----
494 if (moduleSlotTracker) { 0
495 slot = moduleSlotTracker->getLocalSlot(bb); 0
496 } else if (bb->getParent()) { 0
497 ModuleSlotTracker tmpTracker(bb->getModule(), false); 0
498 tmpTracker.incorporateFunction(*bb->getParent()); 0
499 slot = tmpTracker.getLocalSlot(bb); 0
500 } 0
501 ----
502 if (slot == -1) 0
503 os << ""; 0
504 else ----
505 os << slot; 0
506 } ----
507 }; 0
508 ----
509 if (printNameFlags & PrintNameIr) { 0
510 if (const auto *bb = getBasicBlock()) { 0
511 if (bb->hasName()) { 0
512 os << '.' << bb->getName(); 0
513 } else { ----
514 hasAttributes = true; 0
515 os << " ("; 0
516 PrintBBRef(bb); 0
517 } ----
518 } ----
519 } ----
520 ----
521 if (printNameFlags & PrintNameAttributes) { 0
522 if (isMachineBlockAddressTaken()) { 0
523 os << (hasAttributes ? ", " : " ("); 0
524 os << "machine-block-address-taken"; 0
525 hasAttributes = true; 0
526 } ----

634 Register ----
635 MachineBasicBlock::addLiveIn(MCRegister PhysReg, const TargetRegisterClass *RC) { 0
636 assert(getParent() && "MBB must be inserted in function"); 0
637 assert(Register::isPhysicalRegister(PhysReg) && "Expected physreg"); 0
638 assert(RC && "Register class is required"); 0
639 assert((isEHPad() || this == &getParent()->front()) && 0
640 "Only the entry block and landing pads can have physreg live ins"); ----
641 ----
642 bool LiveIn = isLiveIn(PhysReg); 0
643 iterator I = SkipPHIsAndLabels(begin()), E = end(); 0
644 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
645 const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
646 ----
647 // Look for an existing copy. ----
648 if (LiveIn) 0
649 for (;I != E && I->isCopy(); ++I) 0
650 if (I->getOperand(1).getReg() == PhysReg) { 0
651 Register VirtReg = I->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
652 if (!MRI.constrainRegClass(VirtReg, RC)) 0
653 llvm_unreachable("Incompatible live-in register class."); 0
654 return VirtReg; 0
655 } ----
656 ----
657 // No luck, create a virtual register. ----
658 Register VirtReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
659 BuildMI(*this, I, DebugLoc(), TII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY), VirtReg) 0
660 .addReg(PhysReg, RegState::Kill); 0
661 if (!LiveIn) 0
662 addLiveIn(PhysReg); 0
663 return VirtReg; 0
664 } ----

674 static int findJumpTableIndex(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
675 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator TerminatorI = MBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0
676 if (TerminatorI == MBB.end()) 0
677 return -1; 0
678 const MachineInstr &Terminator = *TerminatorI; 0
679 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
680 return TII->getJumpTableIndex(Terminator); 0

682 ----
683 void MachineBasicBlock::updateTerminator( 0
684 MachineBasicBlock *PreviousLayoutSuccessor) { ----
685 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Updating terminators on " << printMBBReference(*this) 0
686 << "\n"); ----
687 ----
688 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
689 // A block with no successors has no concerns with fall-through edges. ----
690 if (this->succ_empty()) 0
691 return; 0
692 ----
693 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
694 SmallVector Cond; 0
695 DebugLoc DL = findBranchDebugLoc(); 0
696 bool B = TII->analyzeBranch(*this, TBB, FBB, Cond); 0
697 (void) B; ----
698 assert(!B && "UpdateTerminators requires analyzable predecessors!"); 0
699 if (Cond.empty()) { 0
700 if (TBB) { 0
701 // The block has an unconditional branch. If its successor is now its ----
702 // layout successor, delete the branch. ----
703 if (isLayoutSuccessor(TBB)) 0
704 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
705 } else { ----
706 // The block has an unconditional fallthrough, or the end of the block is ----
707 // unreachable. ----
708 ----
709 // Unfortunately, whether the end of the block is unreachable is not ----
710 // immediately obvious; we must fall back to checking the successor list, ----
711 // and assuming that if the passed in block is in the succesor list and ----
712 // not an EHPad, it must be the intended target. ----
713 if (!PreviousLayoutSuccessor || !isSuccessor(PreviousLayoutSuccessor) || 0
714 PreviousLayoutSuccessor->isEHPad()) 0
715 return; 0
716 ----
717 // If the unconditional successor block is not the current layout ----
718 // successor, insert a branch to jump to it. ----
719 if (!isLayoutSuccessor(PreviousLayoutSuccessor)) 0
720 TII->insertBranch(*this, PreviousLayoutSuccessor, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
721 } ----
722 return; 0
723 } ----
724 ----
725 if (FBB) { 0
726 // The block has a non-fallthrough conditional branch. If one of its ----
727 // successors is its layout successor, rewrite it to a fallthrough ----
728 // conditional branch. ----
729 if (isLayoutSuccessor(TBB)) { 0
730 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) 0
731 return; 0
732 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
733 TII->insertBranch(*this, FBB, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
734 } else if (isLayoutSuccessor(FBB)) { 0
735 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
736 TII->insertBranch(*this, TBB, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
737 } ----
738 return; 0
739 } ----
740 ----
741 // We now know we're going to fallthrough to PreviousLayoutSuccessor. ----
742 assert(PreviousLayoutSuccessor); 0
743 assert(!PreviousLayoutSuccessor->isEHPad()); 0
744 assert(isSuccessor(PreviousLayoutSuccessor)); 0
745 ----
746 if (PreviousLayoutSuccessor == TBB) { 0
747 // We had a fallthrough to the same basic block as the conditional jump ----
748 // targets. Remove the conditional jump, leaving an unconditional ----
749 // fallthrough or an unconditional jump. ----
750 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
751 if (!isLayoutSuccessor(TBB)) { 0
752 Cond.clear(); 0
753 TII->insertBranch(*this, TBB, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
754 } ----
755 return; 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 // The block has a fallthrough conditional branch. ----
759 if (isLayoutSuccessor(TBB)) { 0
760 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) { 0
761 // We can't reverse the condition, add an unconditional branch. ----
762 Cond.clear(); 0
763 TII->insertBranch(*this, PreviousLayoutSuccessor, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
764 return; 0
765 } ----
766 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
767 TII->insertBranch(*this, PreviousLayoutSuccessor, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
768 } else if (!isLayoutSuccessor(PreviousLayoutSuccessor)) { 0
769 TII->removeBranch(*this); 0
770 TII->insertBranch(*this, TBB, PreviousLayoutSuccessor, Cond, DL); 0
771 } ----
772 } 0
773 ----
774 void MachineBasicBlock::validateSuccProbs() const { 0
775 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
776 int64_t Sum = 0; 0
777 for (auto Prob : Probs) 0
778 Sum += Prob.getNumerator(); 0
779 // Due to precision issue, we assume that the sum of probabilities is one if ----
780 // the difference between the sum of their numerators and the denominator is ----
781 // no greater than the number of successors. ----
782 assert((uint64_t)std::abs(Sum - BranchProbability::getDenominator()) <= 0
783 Probs.size() && ----
784 "The sum of successors's probabilities exceeds one."); ----
785 #endif // NDEBUG ----
786 } 0

807 void MachineBasicBlock::splitSuccessor(MachineBasicBlock *Old, 0
808 MachineBasicBlock *New, ----
809 bool NormalizeSuccProbs) { ----
810 succ_iterator OldI = llvm::find(successors(), Old); 0
811 assert(OldI != succ_end() && "Old is not a successor of this block!"); 0
812 assert(!llvm::is_contained(successors(), New) && 0
813 "New is already a successor of this block!"); ----
814 ----
815 // Add a new successor with equal probability as the original one. Note ----
816 // that we directly copy the probability using the iterator rather than ----
817 // getting a potentially synthetic probability computed when unknown. This ----
818 // preserves the probabilities as-is and then we can renormalize them and ----
819 // query them effectively afterward. ----
820 addSuccessor(New, Probs.empty() ? BranchProbability::getUnknown() 0
821 : *getProbabilityIterator(OldI)); 0
822 if (NormalizeSuccProbs) 0
823 normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
824 } 0

848 ----
849 void MachineBasicBlock::replaceSuccessor(MachineBasicBlock *Old, 0
850 MachineBasicBlock *New) { ----
851 if (Old == New) 0
852 return; 0
853 ----
854 succ_iterator E = succ_end(); 0
855 succ_iterator NewI = E; 0
856 succ_iterator OldI = E; 0
857 for (succ_iterator I = succ_begin(); I != E; ++I) { 0
858 if (*I == Old) { 0
859 OldI = I; 0
860 if (NewI != E) 0
861 break; 0
862 } ----
863 if (*I == New) { 0
864 NewI = I; 0
865 if (OldI != E) 0
866 break; 0
867 } ----
868 } ----
869 assert(OldI != E && "Old is not a successor of this block"); 0
870 ----
871 // If New isn't already a successor, let it take Old's place. ----
872 if (NewI == E) { 0
873 Old->removePredecessor(this); 0
874 New->addPredecessor(this); 0
875 *OldI = New; 0
876 return; 0
877 } ----
878 ----
879 // New is already a successor. ----
880 // Update its probability instead of adding a duplicate edge. ----
881 if (!Probs.empty()) { 0
882 auto ProbIter = getProbabilityIterator(NewI); 0
883 if (!ProbIter->isUnknown()) 0
884 *ProbIter += *getProbabilityIterator(OldI); 0
885 } ----
886 removeSuccessor(OldI); 0
887 } ----

891 if (!Orig->Probs.empty()) 0
892 addSuccessor(*I, Orig->getSuccProbability(I)); 0
893 else ----
894 addSuccessorWithoutProb(*I); 0
895 } 0

962 ----
963 MachineBasicBlock *MachineBasicBlock::getFallThrough(bool JumpToFallThrough) { 0
964 MachineFunction::iterator Fallthrough = getIterator(); 0
965 ++Fallthrough; 0
966 // If FallthroughBlock is off the end of the function, it can't fall through. ----
967 if (Fallthrough == getParent()->end()) 0
968 return nullptr; 0
969 ----
970 // If FallthroughBlock isn't a successor, no fallthrough is possible. ----
971 if (!isSuccessor(&*Fallthrough)) 0
972 return nullptr; 0
973 ----
974 // Analyze the branches, if any, at the end of the block. ----
975 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
976 SmallVector Cond; 0
977 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
978 if (TII->analyzeBranch(*this, TBB, FBB, Cond)) { 0
979 // If we couldn't analyze the branch, examine the last instruction. ----
980 // If the block doesn't end in a known control barrier, assume fallthrough ----
981 // is possible. The isPredicated check is needed because this code can be ----
982 // called during IfConversion, where an instruction which is normally a ----
983 // Barrier is predicated and thus no longer an actual control barrier. ----
984 return (empty() || !back().isBarrier() || TII->isPredicated(back())) 0
985 ? &*Fallthrough 0
986 : nullptr; 0
987 } ----
988 ----
989 // If there is no branch, control always falls through. ----
990 if (!TBB) return &*Fallthrough; 0
991 ----
992 // If there is some explicit branch to the fallthrough block, it can obviously ----
993 // reach, even though the branch should get folded to fall through implicitly. ----
994 if (JumpToFallThrough && (MachineFunction::iterator(TBB) == Fallthrough || 0
995 MachineFunction::iterator(FBB) == Fallthrough)) 0
996 return &*Fallthrough; 0
997 ----
998 // If it's an unconditional branch to some block not the fall through, it ----
999 // doesn't fall through. ----
1000 if (Cond.empty()) return nullptr; 0
1001 ----
1002 // Otherwise, if it is conditional and has no explicit false block, it falls ----
1003 // through. ----
1004 return (FBB == nullptr) ? &*Fallthrough : nullptr; 0
1005 } 0
1006 ----
1007 bool MachineBasicBlock::canFallThrough() { 0
1008 return getFallThrough() != nullptr; 0
1009 } ----
1010 ----
1011 MachineBasicBlock *MachineBasicBlock::splitAt(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1012 bool UpdateLiveIns, ----
1013 LiveIntervals *LIS) { ----
1014 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SplitPoint(&MI); 0
1015 ++SplitPoint; 0
1016 ----
1017 if (SplitPoint == end()) { 0
1018 // Don't bother with a new block. ----
1019 return this; 0
1020 } ----
1021 ----
1022 MachineFunction *MF = getParent(); 0
1023 ----
1024 LivePhysRegs LiveRegs; 0
1025 if (UpdateLiveIns) { 0
1026 // Make sure we add any physregs we define in the block as liveins to the ----
1027 // new block. ----
1028 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Prev(&MI); 0
1029 LiveRegs.init(*MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo()); 0
1030 LiveRegs.addLiveOuts(*this); 0
1031 for (auto I = rbegin(), E = Prev.getReverse(); I != E; ++I) 0
1032 LiveRegs.stepBackward(*I); 0
1033 } ----
1034 ----
1035 MachineBasicBlock *SplitBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(getBasicBlock()); 0
1036 ----
1037 MF->insert(++MachineFunction::iterator(this), SplitBB); 0
1038 SplitBB->splice(SplitBB->begin(), this, SplitPoint, end()); 0
1039 ----
1040 SplitBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(this); 0
1041 addSuccessor(SplitBB); 0
1042 ----
1043 if (UpdateLiveIns) 0
1044 addLiveIns(*SplitBB, LiveRegs); 0
1045 ----
1046 if (LIS) 0
1047 LIS->insertMBBInMaps(SplitBB); 0
1048 ----
1049 return SplitBB; 0
1050 } 0
1051 ----
1052 // Returns `true` if there are possibly other users of the jump table at ----
1053 // `JumpTableIndex` except for the ones in `IgnoreMBB`. ----
1054 static bool jumpTableHasOtherUses(const MachineFunction &MF, 0
1055 const MachineBasicBlock &IgnoreMBB, ----
1056 int JumpTableIndex) { ----
1057 assert(JumpTableIndex >= 0 && "need valid index"); 0
1058 const MachineJumpTableInfo &MJTI = *MF.getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1059 const MachineJumpTableEntry &MJTE = MJTI.getJumpTables()[JumpTableIndex]; 0
1060 // Take any basic block from the table; every user of the jump table must ----
1061 // show up in the predecessor list. ----
1062 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = nullptr; 0
1063 for (MachineBasicBlock *B : MJTE.MBBs) { 0
1064 if (B != nullptr) { 0
1065 MBB = B; 0
1066 break; 0
1067 } ----
1068 } ----
1069 if (MBB == nullptr) 0
1070 return true; // can't rule out other users if there isn't any block. 0
1071 const TargetInstrInfo &TII = *MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
1072 SmallVector Cond; 0
1073 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
1074 if (Pred == &IgnoreMBB) 0
1075 continue; 0
1076 MachineBasicBlock *DummyT = nullptr; 0
1077 MachineBasicBlock *DummyF = nullptr; 0
1078 Cond.clear(); 0
1079 if (!TII.analyzeBranch(*Pred, DummyT, DummyF, Cond, 0
1080 /*AllowModify=*/false)) { ----
1081 // analyzable direct jump ----
1082 continue; 0
1083 } ----
1084 int PredJTI = findJumpTableIndex(*Pred); 0
1085 if (PredJTI >= 0) { 0
1086 if (PredJTI == JumpTableIndex) 0
1087 return true; 0
1088 continue; 0
1089 } ----
1090 // Be conservative for unanalyzable jumps. ----
1091 return true; 0
1092 } ----
1093 return false; 0
1094 } 0
1095 ----
1096 MachineBasicBlock *MachineBasicBlock::SplitCriticalEdge( 0
1097 MachineBasicBlock *Succ, Pass &P, ----
1098 std::vector> *LiveInSets) { ----
1099 if (!canSplitCriticalEdge(Succ)) 0
1100 return nullptr; 0
1101 ----
1102 MachineFunction *MF = getParent(); 0
1103 MachineBasicBlock *PrevFallthrough = getNextNode(); 0
1104 DebugLoc DL; // FIXME: this is nowhere 0
1105 ----
1106 MachineBasicBlock *NMBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
1107 NMBB->setCallFrameSize(Succ->getCallFrameSize()); 0
1108 ----
1109 // Is there an indirect jump with jump table? ----
1110 bool ChangedIndirectJump = false; 0
1111 int JTI = findJumpTableIndex(*this); 0
1112 if (JTI >= 0) { 0
1113 MachineJumpTableInfo &MJTI = *MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1114 MJTI.ReplaceMBBInJumpTable(JTI, Succ, NMBB); 0
1115 ChangedIndirectJump = true; 0
1116 } ----
1117 ----
1118 MF->insert(std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(this)), NMBB); 0
1119 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Splitting critical edge: " << printMBBReference(*this) 0
1120 << " -- " << printMBBReference(*NMBB) << " -- " ----
1121 << printMBBReference(*Succ) << '\n'); ----
1122 ----
1123 LiveIntervals *LIS = P.getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
1124 SlotIndexes *Indexes = P.getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
1125 if (LIS) 0
1126 LIS->insertMBBInMaps(NMBB); 0
1127 else if (Indexes) 0
1128 Indexes->insertMBBInMaps(NMBB); 0
1129 ----
1130 // On some targets like Mips, branches may kill virtual registers. Make sure ----
1131 // that LiveVariables is properly updated after updateTerminator replaces the ----
1132 // terminators. ----
1133 LiveVariables *LV = P.getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
1134 ----
1135 // Collect a list of virtual registers killed by the terminators. ----
1136 SmallVector KilledRegs; 0
1137 if (LV) 0
1138 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
1139 llvm::make_range(getFirstInstrTerminator(), instr_end())) { 0
1140 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) { 0
1141 if (MO.getReg() == 0 || !MO.isKill() || MO.isUndef()) 0
1142 continue; 0
1143 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1144 if (Reg.isPhysical() || LV->getVarInfo(Reg).removeKill(MI)) { 0
1145 KilledRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1146 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing terminator kill: " << MI); 0
1147 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
1148 } ----
1149 } ----
1150 } ----
1151 ----
1152 SmallVector UsedRegs; 0
1153 if (LIS) { 0
1154 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
1155 llvm::make_range(getFirstInstrTerminator(), instr_end())) { 0
1156 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1157 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.getReg() == 0) 0
1158 continue; 0
1159 ----
1160 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1161 if (!is_contained(UsedRegs, Reg)) 0
1162 UsedRegs.push_back(Reg); 0
1163 } ----
1164 } ----
1165 } ----
1166 ----
1167 ReplaceUsesOfBlockWith(Succ, NMBB); 0
1168 ----
1169 // If updateTerminator() removes instructions, we need to remove them from ----
1170 // SlotIndexes. ----
1171 SmallVector Terminators; 0
1172 if (Indexes) { 0
1173 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
1174 llvm::make_range(getFirstInstrTerminator(), instr_end())) 0
1175 Terminators.push_back(&MI); 0
1176 } ----
1177 ----
1178 // Since we replaced all uses of Succ with NMBB, that should also be treated ----
1179 // as the fallthrough successor ----
1180 if (Succ == PrevFallthrough) 0
1181 PrevFallthrough = NMBB; 0
1182 ----
1183 if (!ChangedIndirectJump) 0
1184 updateTerminator(PrevFallthrough); 0
1185 ----
1186 if (Indexes) { 0
1187 SmallVector NewTerminators; 0
1188 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
1189 llvm::make_range(getFirstInstrTerminator(), instr_end())) 0
1190 NewTerminators.push_back(&MI); 0
1191 ----
1192 for (MachineInstr *Terminator : Terminators) { 0
1193 if (!is_contained(NewTerminators, Terminator)) 0
1194 Indexes->removeMachineInstrFromMaps(*Terminator); 0
1195 } ----
1196 } 0
1197 ----
1198 // Insert unconditional "jump Succ" instruction in NMBB if necessary. ----
1199 NMBB->addSuccessor(Succ); 0
1200 if (!NMBB->isLayoutSuccessor(Succ)) { 0
1201 SmallVector Cond; 0
1202 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
1203 TII->insertBranch(*NMBB, Succ, nullptr, Cond, DL); 0
1204 ----
1205 if (Indexes) { 0
1206 for (MachineInstr &MI : NMBB->instrs()) { 0
1207 // Some instructions may have been moved to NMBB by updateTerminator(), ----
1208 // so we first remove any instruction that already has an index. ----
1209 if (Indexes->hasIndex(MI)) 0
1210 Indexes->removeMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1211 Indexes->insertMachineInstrInMaps(MI); 0
1212 } ----
1213 } ----
1214 } 0
1215 ----
1216 // Fix PHI nodes in Succ so they refer to NMBB instead of this. ----
1217 Succ->replacePhiUsesWith(this, NMBB); 0
1218 ----
1219 // Inherit live-ins from the successor ----
1220 for (const auto &LI : Succ->liveins()) 0
1221 NMBB->addLiveIn(LI); 0
1222 ----
1223 // Update LiveVariables. ----
1224 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1225 if (LV) { 0
1226 // Restore kills of virtual registers that were killed by the terminators. ----
1227 while (!KilledRegs.empty()) { 0
1228 Register Reg = KilledRegs.pop_back_val(); 0
1229 for (instr_iterator I = instr_end(), E = instr_begin(); I != E;) { 0
1230 if (!(--I)->addRegisterKilled(Reg, TRI, /* AddIfNotFound= */ false)) 0
1231 continue; 0
1232 if (Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1233 LV->getVarInfo(Reg).Kills.push_back(&*I); 0
1234 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Restored terminator kill: " << *I); 0
1235 break; 0
1236 } ----
1237 } ----
1238 // Update relevant live-through information. ----
1239 if (LiveInSets != nullptr) 0
1240 LV->addNewBlock(NMBB, this, Succ, *LiveInSets); 0
1241 else ----
1242 LV->addNewBlock(NMBB, this, Succ); 0
1243 } ----
1244 ----
1245 if (LIS) { 0
1246 // After splitting the edge and updating SlotIndexes, live intervals may be ----
1247 // in one of two situations, depending on whether this block was the last in ----
1248 // the function. If the original block was the last in the function, all ----
1249 // live intervals will end prior to the beginning of the new split block. If ----
1250 // the original block was not at the end of the function, all live intervals ----
1251 // will extend to the end of the new split block. ----
1252 ----
1253 bool isLastMBB = ----
1254 std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(NMBB)) == getParent()->end(); 0
1255 ----
1256 SlotIndex StartIndex = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(this); 0
1257 SlotIndex PrevIndex = StartIndex.getPrevSlot(); 0
1258 SlotIndex EndIndex = Indexes->getMBBEndIdx(NMBB); 0
1259 ----
1260 // Find the registers used from NMBB in PHIs in Succ. ----
1261 SmallSet PHISrcRegs; 0
1262 for (MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator 0
1263 I = Succ->instr_begin(), E = Succ->instr_end(); 0
1264 I != E && I->isPHI(); ++I) { 0
1265 for (unsigned ni = 1, ne = I->getNumOperands(); ni != ne; ni += 2) { 0
1266 if (I->getOperand(ni+1).getMBB() == NMBB) { 0
1267 MachineOperand &MO = I->getOperand(ni); 0
1268 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1269 PHISrcRegs.insert(Reg); 0
1270 if (MO.isUndef()) 0
1271 continue; 0
1272 ----
1273 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
1274 VNInfo *VNI = LI.getVNInfoAt(PrevIndex); 0
1275 assert(VNI && 0
1276 "PHI sources should be live out of their predecessors."); ----
1277 LI.addSegment(LiveInterval::Segment(StartIndex, EndIndex, VNI)); 0
1278 } ----
1279 } ----
1280 } ----
1281 ----
1282 MachineRegisterInfo *MRI = &getParent()->getRegInfo(); 0
1283 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MRI->getNumVirtRegs(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1284 Register Reg = Register::index2VirtReg(i); 0
1285 if (PHISrcRegs.count(Reg) || !LIS->hasInterval(Reg)) 0
1286 continue; 0
1287 ----
1288 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
1289 if (!LI.liveAt(PrevIndex)) 0
1290 continue; 0
1291 ----
1292 bool isLiveOut = LI.liveAt(LIS->getMBBStartIdx(Succ)); 0
1293 if (isLiveOut && isLastMBB) { 0
1294 VNInfo *VNI = LI.getVNInfoAt(PrevIndex); 0
1295 assert(VNI && "LiveInterval should have VNInfo where it is live."); 0
1296 LI.addSegment(LiveInterval::Segment(StartIndex, EndIndex, VNI)); 0
1297 } else if (!isLiveOut && !isLastMBB) { 0
1298 LI.removeSegment(StartIndex, EndIndex); 0
1299 } ----
1300 } ----
1301 ----
1302 // Update all intervals for registers whose uses may have been modified by ----
1303 // updateTerminator(). ----
1304 LIS->repairIntervalsInRange(this, getFirstTerminator(), end(), UsedRegs); 0
1305 } 0
1306 ----
1307 if (MachineDominatorTree *MDT = 0
1308 P.getAnalysisIfAvailable()) 0
1309 MDT->recordSplitCriticalEdge(this, Succ, NMBB); 0
1310 ----
1311 if (MachineLoopInfo *MLI = P.getAnalysisIfAvailable()) 0
1312 if (MachineLoop *TIL = MLI->getLoopFor(this)) { 0
1313 // If one or the other blocks were not in a loop, the new block is not ----
1314 // either, and thus LI doesn't need to be updated. ----
1315 if (MachineLoop *DestLoop = MLI->getLoopFor(Succ)) { 0
1316 if (TIL == DestLoop) { 0
1317 // Both in the same loop, the NMBB joins loop. ----
1318 DestLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NMBB, MLI->getBase()); 0
1319 } else if (TIL->contains(DestLoop)) { 0
1320 // Edge from an outer loop to an inner loop. Add to the outer loop. ----
1321 TIL->addBasicBlockToLoop(NMBB, MLI->getBase()); 0
1322 } else if (DestLoop->contains(TIL)) { 0
1323 // Edge from an inner loop to an outer loop. Add to the outer loop. ----
1324 DestLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NMBB, MLI->getBase()); 0
1325 } else { ----
1326 // Edge from two loops with no containment relation. Because these ----
1327 // are natural loops, we know that the destination block must be the ----
1328 // header of its loop (adding a branch into a loop elsewhere would ----
1329 // create an irreducible loop). ----
1330 assert(DestLoop->getHeader() == Succ && 0
1331 "Should not create irreducible loops!"); ----
1332 if (MachineLoop *P = DestLoop->getParentLoop()) 0
1333 P->addBasicBlockToLoop(NMBB, MLI->getBase()); 0
1334 } ----
1335 } ----
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 return NMBB; 0
1339 } 0
1340 ----
1341 bool MachineBasicBlock::canSplitCriticalEdge( 0
1342 const MachineBasicBlock *Succ) const { ----
1343 // Splitting the critical edge to a landing pad block is non-trivial. Don't do ----
1344 // it in this generic function. ----
1345 if (Succ->isEHPad()) 0
1346 return false; 0
1347 ----
1348 // Splitting the critical edge to a callbr's indirect block isn't advised. ----
1349 // Don't do it in this generic function. ----
1350 if (Succ->isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) 0
1351 return false; 0
1352 ----
1353 const MachineFunction *MF = getParent(); 0
1354 // Performance might be harmed on HW that implements branching using exec mask ----
1355 // where both sides of the branches are always executed. ----
1356 if (MF->getTarget().requiresStructuredCFG()) 0
1357 return false; 0
1358 ----
1359 // Do we have an Indirect jump with a jumptable that we can rewrite? ----
1360 int JTI = findJumpTableIndex(*this); 0
1361 if (JTI >= 0 && !jumpTableHasOtherUses(*MF, *this, JTI)) 0
1362 return true; 0
1363 ----
1364 // We may need to update this's terminator, but we can't do that if ----
1365 // analyzeBranch fails. ----
1366 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
1367 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
1368 SmallVector Cond; 0
1369 // AnalyzeBanch should modify this, since we did not allow modification. ----
1370 if (TII->analyzeBranch(*const_cast(this), TBB, FBB, Cond, 0
1371 /*AllowModify*/ false)) ----
1372 return false; 0
1373 ----
1374 // Avoid bugpoint weirdness: A block may end with a conditional branch but ----
1375 // jumps to the same MBB is either case. We have duplicate CFG edges in that ----
1376 // case that we can't handle. Since this never happens in properly optimized ----
1377 // code, just skip those edges. ----
1378 if (TBB && TBB == FBB) { 0
1379 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Won't split critical edge after degenerate " 0
1380 << printMBBReference(*this) << '\n'); ----
1381 return false; 0
1382 } ----
1383 return true; 0
1384 } 0

1391 MI->unbundleFromSucc(); 0

1397 } 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

1438 /// Given a machine basic block that branched to 'Old', change the code and CFG ----
1439 /// so that it branches to 'New' instead. ----
1440 void MachineBasicBlock::ReplaceUsesOfBlockWith(MachineBasicBlock *Old, 0
1441 MachineBasicBlock *New) { ----
1442 assert(Old != New && "Cannot replace self with self!"); 0
1443 ----
1444 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator I = instr_end(); 0
1445 while (I != instr_begin()) { 0
1446 --I; 0
1447 if (!I->isTerminator()) break; 0
1448 ----
1449 // Scan the operands of this machine instruction, replacing any uses of Old ----
1450 // with New. ----
1451 for (unsigned i = 0, e = I->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
1452 if (I->getOperand(i).isMBB() && 0
1453 I->getOperand(i).getMBB() == Old) 0
1454 I->getOperand(i).setMBB(New); 0
1455 } ----
1456 ----
1457 // Update the successor information. ----
1458 replaceSuccessor(Old, New); 0
1459 } 0

1461 void MachineBasicBlock::replacePhiUsesWith(MachineBasicBlock *Old, 0
1462 MachineBasicBlock *New) { ----

1464 for (unsigned i = 2, e = MI.getNumOperands() + 1; i != e; i += 2) { 0
1465 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(i); 0
1466 if (MO.getMBB() == Old) 0
1467 MO.setMBB(New); 0
1468 } ----
1469 } 0

1583 /// Return whether (physical) register "Reg" has been ined and not ed ----

1585 /// ----
1586 /// Search is localised to a neighborhood of ----

1589 MachineBasicBlock::LivenessQueryResult ----
1590 MachineBasicBlock::computeRegisterLiveness(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, 0
1591 MCRegister Reg, const_iterator Before, ----
1592 unsigned Neighborhood) const { ----
1593 unsigned N = Neighborhood; 0
1594 ----
1595 // Try searching forwards from Before, looking for reads or defs. ----
1596 const_iterator I(Before); 0
1597 for (; I != end() && N > 0; ++I) { 0
1598 if (I->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
1599 continue; 0
1600 ----
1601 --N; 0
1602 ----
1603 PhysRegInfo Info = AnalyzePhysRegInBundle(*I, Reg, TRI); 0
1604 ----
1605 // Register is live when we read it here. ----
1606 if (Info.Read) 0
1607 return LQR_Live; 0
1608 // Register is dead if we can fully overwrite or clobber it here. ----
1609 if (Info.FullyDefined || Info.Clobbered) 0
1610 return LQR_Dead; 0
1611 } ----
1612 ----
1613 // If we reached the end, it is safe to clobber Reg at the end of a block of ----
1614 // no successor has it live in. ----
1615 if (I == end()) { 0
1616 for (MachineBasicBlock *S : successors()) { 0
1617 for (const MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair &LI : S->liveins()) { 0
1618 if (TRI->regsOverlap(LI.PhysReg, Reg)) 0
1619 return LQR_Live; 0
1620 } ----
1621 } ----
1622 ----
1623 return LQR_Dead; 0
1624 } ----
1625 ----
1626 ----
1627 N = Neighborhood; 0
1628 ----
1629 // Start by searching backwards from Before, looking for kills, reads or defs. ----
1630 I = const_iterator(Before); 0
1631 // If this is the first insn in the block, don't search backwards. ----
1632 if (I != begin()) { 0
1633 do { ----
1634 --I; 0
1635 ----
1636 if (I->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
1637 continue; 0
1638 ----
1639 --N; 0
1640 ----
1641 PhysRegInfo Info = AnalyzePhysRegInBundle(*I, Reg, TRI); 0
1642 ----
1643 // Defs happen after uses so they take precedence if both are present. ----
1644 ----
1645 // Register is dead after a dead def of the full register. ----
1646 if (Info.DeadDef) 0
1647 return LQR_Dead; 0
1648 // Register is (at least partially) live after a def. ----
1649 if (Info.Defined) { 0
1650 if (!Info.PartialDeadDef) 0
1651 return LQR_Live; 0
1652 // As soon as we saw a partial definition (dead or not), ----
1653 // we cannot tell if the value is partial live without ----
1654 // tracking the lanemasks. We are not going to do this, ----
1655 // so fall back on the remaining of the analysis. ----
1656 break; 0
1657 } ----
1658 // Register is dead after a full kill or clobber and no def. ----
1659 if (Info.Killed || Info.Clobbered) 0
1660 return LQR_Dead; 0
1661 // Register must be live if we read it. ----
1662 if (Info.Read) 0
1663 return LQR_Live; 0
1664 ----
1665 } while (I != begin() && N > 0); 0
1666 } ----
1667 ----
1668 // If all the instructions before this in the block are debug instructions, ----
1669 // skip over them. ----
1670 while (I != begin() && std::prev(I)->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) 0
1671 --I; 0
1672 ----
1673 // Did we get to the start of the block? ----
1674 if (I == begin()) { 0
1675 // If so, the register's state is definitely defined by the live-in state. ----
1676 for (const MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair &LI : liveins()) 0
1677 if (TRI->regsOverlap(LI.PhysReg, Reg)) 0
1678 return LQR_Live; 0
1679 ----
1680 return LQR_Dead; 0
1681 } ----
1682 ----
1683 // At this point we have no idea of the liveness of the register. ----
1684 return LQR_Unknown; 0
1685 } ----
